f=Engineering/raj/custom/service-patterns/SKILL.md · in=service-patterns raj makes backend services behave under real conditions: idempotency retries safe, timeouts circuit breakers one slow dependency doesn't cascade, queues work shouldn't block request, clear service boundaries system stays understandable. It's reliability half backend API contract (api-standards) says what service does; says survives. · p=Services fail production predictable ways: retried payment charges twice (no idempotency), slow downstream hangs thread (no timeout), traffic spike melts synchronous pipeline (no queue), cascading failure takes down everything (no circuit breaker). patterns accumulated answers dev's "everything fails time," applied service layer. · wu=Triggers: "design service," "should async," "idempotency," "retry/timeout," "circuit breaker," "queue this," "service boundary," any operation mutates state, calls dependency, slow work. · st:/ Protocol=`A service/operation to design \· -> MUTATION? → idempotency key so retries are safe (never double-charge/double-write) \· -> CALLS A DEPENDENCY? → timeout (always) + retry-with-backoff (idempotent only) + circuit breaker \· -> SLOW / non-blocking work? → queue + background worker, not a held request \· -> BOUNDARY: one service owns one responsibility; shared state across boundaries is a smell` · in=**Idempotency mutation.** Any state-changing operation carries idempotency key retry (network blip, client double-tap, ops's deploy retry) doesn't double-apply. classic failure retried request charging twice designed out, hoped away. **Timeout dependency call; breaker flaky ones.** call database, API, service unbounded missing timeout means one slow dependency exhausts thread/connection pool cascades. Circuit breakers stop hammering downed dependency; retries (with backoff) idempotent operations. **Async slow work.** Work doesn't need block response email, image processing, report generation goes queue background worker. request thread held slow work scaling ceiling DoS surface. **One service, one responsibility.** Clear boundaries; service owning two unrelated things, two services sharing mutable store, coupling data bugs breed. Boundaries map data model's ownership (dana). **Own failure mode.** dependency, answer "what happens it's down" degrade gracefully, queue later, fail cleanly right error (api-standards' shape). unowned failure mode dev's rejected architecture, service edition. **Complexity cost real.** pattern adds moving parts; apply them failure they prevent real, everywhere (dev's boring-is-a-feature). queue work that's always fast complexity nothing. · of=`## Service: [name/operation] \· Mutation → idempotency: [key strategy / n/a] \· Dependency calls → [timeout ✓ \· retry(idempotent) \· breaker] \· Slow work → [sync / queued + worker] \· Boundary: [single responsibility ✓] \· Failure modes: [dependency down → degrade/queue/fail-clean]` · pr=**Idempotency mutation** retries safe; double-charge design failure., **Timeout dependency; breaker flaky** unbounded call cascades., **Async slow work** held request threads scaling ceiling DoS surface., **One service, one responsibility** shared mutable state across boundaries smell., **Own failure mode** "what it's down" answer, design rejected., **Patterns cost moving parts** apply failure real, everywhere. · f=Early/simple service start timeouts idempotency (the cheap, always-worth-it pair); add queues/breakers failure they prevent becomes real, preemptively., Idempotency hard operation make (natural keys, dedup) before shipping retryable mutation; non-idempotent mutation behind retry bug., Existing service missing add incrementally, prioritized which failure already bitten (ops's incidents point way). · b:with Other Skills=**api-standards** (sibling): contract edge; behavior behind it., **data-access-discipline** (sibling): calls get timeouts pooling here; N+1 avoidance there., **ops/incident-response**: production failures reveal missing patterns; post-mortems route here; ops's reliability skill's downstream., **axiom**: complexity retry/queue logic worst-case behavior., **dana**: service boundaries reflect data ownership., **cypher**: unbounded work missing timeouts DoS surfaces (L10) cypher tests. · h2:Stack Notes (dated)=`assets/stack-notes-node-backend-2026-07.md` Node.js layering/caching/error/rate-limit mechanics. Applies stack-profile names Node.js; adopted marketplace (ECC) 2026-07-10; method conflicts resolve skill.